The photography for the true orthos was flown on 3/24/2003.  The altitude for both flight dates was 3600'.  The photography was captured with a Ziess RMK Top 15 equipped with FMC (Forward-Motion Compensation) and a Zeiss TAS gyro-stabilized mount. The photography was scanned with a Z/I Imaging Photoscan 2000 photogrammetric scanner at 14 micron resolution.  The orthophotos were generated using KLT Ortho software and have a pixel resolution of .5', and the mosaics were put together from the orthos using OrthoVista software.</procdesc>         <proccont>
